    <h1>Careers</h1>
    <p>
        <strong>Communications Technology, Inc. (CTI)</strong> is an independently, locally
        owned voice and data communications company serving Michigan businesses for over
        25 years. <strong>CTI</strong> is a one source solution for ordering dial tone and
        high-speed Internet, providing voice and data cabling, and installation and support
        of business phones and computer networks. The company takes a consultative approach
        to its customers; needs and makes recommendations based on over 150 years of combined
        experience and expertise. <strong>CTI</strong> actively supports the community through
        its involvement with non-profit and other charitable organizations. <strong>CTI</strong>'s
        goal is to add value, differentiate its services, and deliver strategic technologies
        with integrity and innovation resulting in the highest level of customer profitability,
        satisfaction and competitive advantage.
    </p>
    <h3>CTI is always looking for qualified and talented people to join our team.</h3>
    <h4>Customer Advocate</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Enhance the relationship and value for our existing customer base by managing accounts,
            driving new and recurring revenue and initiating sales activity and customer contact.
        </li>
        <li>Proven computer skills including Microsoft Excel and Word and database management.
        </li>
        <li>Strong organizational skills and knowledge of analyzing existing telephone / cell
            phone bills.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4>Computer Network Technician</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Design, install and support local are networks (LANs) and larger wide area networks
            (WANs) for business, education, government and health care institutions. </li>
        <li>Familiarity with computer and networking terminology, protocols and hardware.
        </li>
        <li>Possess knowledge of necessary software including different operation systems such
            as Windows, Novell and UNIX. </li>
        <li>Understand basic network architecture models such as peer to peer and client server.
        </li>
        <li>Work with little or no direct supervision. </li>
        <li>Formal training (i.e. college credits / degree or other formal extra curricular
            schooling / experience necessary.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4>Voice Technician</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Proficient in all levels of installing, testing and repairing of telephone and peripheral
            equipment, video equipment, paging equipment and network wiring and connectivity.
        </li>
        <li>Intimate knowledge of various voice and data circuitry, network and Internet telephony
            applications, paging and video equipment. </li>
        <li>Work with little or no supervision and have ability to import this knowledge to
            other technicians for training purposes. </li>
        <li>Formal training (i.e. college credits / degree or other formal extra curricular
            schooling / experience necessary. </li>
    </ul>
    <h4 id="salesExec">Sales Executive</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Responsible for generating new business revenue with local, regional and national
            companies by prospecting, preparing and presenting proposals to corporate decision
            makers. </li>
        <li>Build interactive relationships followed by an introductory needs analysis / discovery
            meeting utilizing a consultative sales approach. </li>
        <li>Have knowledge of telecom equipment and applications, strong solution selling skills
            and a documented record of sales achievements. </li>
        <li>Excellent oral and written communication skills.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4 id="service_coordinator">Service Coordinator / Dispatcher</h4>
    <p>
        We are in need of a reliable, well organized, self-motivated Service Coordinator / Dispatcher to act as a communication point for emergency and non-emergency calls.
        <br />
        The ideal candidate must be an excellent communicator and able to remain calm and composed,especially in emergency situations. They must be able to multi-task as well as take appropriate action with little supervision.
    </p>
    <p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Receive emergency and non-emergency calls and record significant information.

        </li>
        <li>Address problems and requests by transmitting information and/or providing solutions

        </li>
        <li>Prioritize calls according to urgency and importance

        </li>
        <li>Monitor route and status of field techs to coordinate and prioritize their schedule

        </li>
        <li>Enter data in software and maintain logs and records of calls, activities and other information

        </li>
        <li>Maintain warehouse with appropriate quantities of service related materials and stock</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Proven experience as dispatcher or relevant position.

        </li>
        <li>Tech-savvy with knowledge of data networks, business telephone systems and camera systems.

        </li>
        <li>Outstanding organizational and multitasking abilities

        </li>
        <li>Active listener with excellent communication skills</li>
    </ul>
